# {{.ProjectName}}

Gemini extension scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

## Status

- Packaging contract: `gemini-extension.json`, shared MCP, primary root context, and Gemini-native extension assets
- Lifecycle: copy-install for releases, `gemini extensions link` for local development, restart Gemini CLI after changes
- Platform family: `extension_package`
- Launcher contract: `none`
- Runtime claim: `packaging-only target`

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai render .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform gemini --strict
```

## Target Files

- `plugin.yaml`: portable package manifest
- no `launcher.yaml`: Gemini packaging does not use the executable launcher contract
- `targets/gemini/package.yaml`: compact Gemini extension metadata such as `context_file_name`, `exclude_tools`, and `plan_directory`
- `contexts/GEMINI.md`: primary shared extension context starter
- `targets/gemini/commands/`: TOML slash commands
- `targets/gemini/hooks/`: `hooks/hooks.json`
- `targets/gemini/policies/`: extension policy files
- `targets/gemini/settings/`: install-time settings that render into `settings[]`
- `targets/gemini/themes/`: extension themes that render into `themes[]`
- `targets/gemini/manifest.extra.json`: forward-compatible escape hatch for future Gemini manifest fields

Generated artifacts come from `plugin-kit-ai render`:

- `gemini-extension.json`
- selected root context file, usually `GEMINI.md`
- native Gemini file trees copied from `targets/gemini/commands/`, `targets/gemini/hooks/`, and `targets/gemini/policies/`

## Stable Default

- Keep shared concepts in portable roots: `mcp/`, `skills/`, and `agents/`
- Keep Gemini-only semantics in `targets/gemini/...`
- Treat `plugin-kit-ai validate --strict` as the CI gate for extension packaging correctness

This scaffold targets official Gemini CLI extension packaging. It does not claim runtime parity with Claude or Codex.
